    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-23T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-23T11:00:00-05:00" n="288"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/967: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Barcelona</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-23T18:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 23, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 24—9:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>987. Embassy’s 942, April 16, 6 p.m. Revised estimates made by Military Attaché
                    place number of Americans now serving with Government forces at 1250, of whom
                    300 are in hospitals and 150 in Valencia. The total thus far killed and missing
                    in action is put at 500. A few continue to arrive.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
